<DOCNO> AP890825-0009 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a state law that would have barred the 
sale or rental of violent videotapes to children was blocked 
thursday by a federal judge who said the measure might clash with 
the right of free speech 
under the law signed june 20 by gov john ashcroft video 
retailers could be fined as much as 200 for renting or selling 
socalled slasher films to children under age 17 the law was 
to take effect monday 
the gray areas are the important ones in this case arent 
they said us district judge b brook bartlett because thats 
where a prosecutor and store owner could have a difference of 
opinion that could get the store owner in trouble 
the measure which would also apply to videos considered 
pornographic under missouri law would require stores to maintain 
separate display areas for violent films 
video industry groups and retailers challenged the law with a 
class action lawsuit and sought the temporary restraining order 
arguing that the law would force video store owners to decide by 
monday which videos fell under the law 
the lawsuit names attorney general william webster and cole 
county prosecutor richard callahan contends the law violates 
constitutional rights of free expression equal protection and due 
process of law 
the missouri law restricts videos that based on contemporary 
community standards would be interpreted by the average person to 
have a tendency to cater or appeal to morbid interest in 
violence for persons under 17 that depict violence that is 
patently offensive and lack serious literary artistic 
political or scientific value 
the lawsuit said the law would require video retailers to limit 
sale and rental of videos that are not obscene and not 
constitutionally subject to restriction under state or federal law 
the lawsuit said terms such as violence and morbid have 
no certain meaning it also criticized the law for applying 
arbitrarily to videos only and not to identical expression in 
television movie theaters and magazines 
the lawsuit was filed by the video software dealers association 
the missouri retailers association the missouri grocers association 
and the motion picture association of america and two retailers 
video express inc of kansas city and baileys cc enterprises inc 
</TEXT>
