the united states maintains clark air base the subic bay naval 
base and four smaller installations under an agreement that expires 
in september 1991 talks are expected to begin late this year on 
extending the agreement 
mrs aquino refuses to say whether she supports a new agreement 
which must be approved by twothirds of the 23member senate on 
thursday 12 senators called for closing the bases in 1991 showing 
the aquino administration lacks the votes for ratification 
