units this year down 5 percent from 1988 in part because higher 
costs are pricing the entrylevel buyer out of the market 
the downswing in rates is pulling some buyers off the 
sidelines said nar president ira gribin adding that the impact 
of lower mortgage rates is likely to be steady tradeup sales 
rather than a sales surge among firsttime buyers 
