<TEXT>
a state appeals court friday overturned 
the firstdegree assault conviction of an aidsinfected inmate who 
bit a prison guard but said there was enough evidence to support a 
lesser assault charge 
in a 41 ruling the alabama court of criminal appeals said there 
was insufficient evidence to uphold adam brocks conviction for 
firstdegree assault and his 15year sentence 
but the judges said the facts supported a conviction on a 
lesser charge of thirddegree assault the appeals court sent the 
case back to limestone county circuit court for brock to be 
sentenced for thirddegree assault a misdemeanor punishable by a 
maximum one year in jail 
firstdegree assault is a felony involving the use of a deadly 
weapon or a dangerous instrument to cause serious physical injury 
brock 31 is confined in a special unit at the limestone 
correctional facility in capshaw for inmates infected with the 
acquired immune deficiency syndrome virus 
in january 1988 brock scuffled with officer jim gates when gates 
tried to remove prohibited ink pens from brocks cell gates was 
bitten on the arm but three subsequent tests showed no traces of 
the aids virus 
brock was charged with attempted murder in the first criminal 
case ever brought in alabama involving a bite by a person infected 
with the aids virus but a jury convicted him of a reduced charge of 
firstdegree assault 
the appeals court in a ruling written by judge william bowen 
said the state failed to prove that brock used his mouth and teeth 
under circumstances highly capable of causing death or serious 
physical injury 
this court can not take judicial notice that biting is a means 
capable of spreading aids while aids may very well be transmitted 
through a human bite there was no evidence to that effect at trial 
and we do not believe that is established scientific fact the 
court ruled 
the court said however that the state did prove elements of 
assault in the third degree 
under alabama law a person can be convicted of thirddegree 
assault if while trying to prevent a peace officer from performing 
his duty the person causes physical injury to anyone 
brock originally was sentenced to 12 years in prison in 1977 for 
robbery and buying and receiving stolen property in jefferson 
county hale said 
