martin marietta corp said its new orleans 
plant won a 1797 billion contract thursday to produce 60 more 
external tanks to fuel the nations space shuttle through mid1997 
the tanks made of aluminum steel alloys and titanium are 
produced by martin mariettas manned space systems co at nasas 
michoud assembly facility near new orleans the plant employs about 
3500 people 
each of the huge external tanks 154 feet long and 28 feet in 
diameter supplies more than 500000 gallons of liquid hydrogen fuel 
and liquid oxygen oxidizer to the orbiter during liftoff and ascent 
the supercold propellants are fed to the orbiters engines at a 
rate of 1035 gallons per second emptying the tank in about 8 
minutes when loaded the tanks weigh 1676 million pounds when 
empty 66000 pounds 
when loaded the tank is the largest and heaviest part of the 
shuttle and its only major nonreusable element it is comprised of 
about 481450 components 
the first tank to be built under the new contract is to be 
completed by late 1991 and the last by mid1997 the company said 
under previous contracts martin marietta has produced 52 of 59 
external tanks 
