semel was cited for internal trading rules violations that also 
are being examined in civil and criminal probes at comex and three 
other exchanges announced in may by the cftc and justice department 
the probes are unrelated to a longstanding probe of chicagos 
commodity markets that recently yielded 46 indictments for 
racketeering and fraud 
a government official familiar with the new york investigations 
confirmed thursday that semel is one of many traders whose 
actions are being examined the official who asked not to be named 
said the probes include the same types of violations cited by comex 
