<TEXT>
a federal judge on friday ruled against 
farmers insurance groups attempt to throw a wrench in takeover 
plans by a british investment group 
at issue is the right of a state agency in this case the texas 
insurance commissioner to review a takeover bid involving foreign 
companies hoylake investments of london has made an offer for 
farmers parent bat industries plc also based in britain farmers 
is based in california 
hoylake has filed lawsuits in texas and eight other states 
claiming that it is unconstitutional to subject hoylakes takeover 
bid to state regulatory review the companys position is that the 
hoylake offer is strictly a british securities transaction out of 
the reach of state regulatory review 
farmers had filed motions to dismiss hoylakes case in texas 
us district judge walter smith denied that request on friday at 
the same time smith denied hoylakes request for a preliminary 
injunction against the state insurance commission review 
hoylake said it would appeal the judges ruling as soon as 
possible 
hoylake attorney laurence tribe characterized the takeover bid as 
a whollyforeign securities transaction subjecting it to state 
agency reviews not only exceeds the constitutional limitations on 
state authority but imposes an unfair burden on foreign 
companies he said 
similar lawsuits have been filed in eight other states where 
farmers does business california washington oregon arizona 
ohio idaho illinois and kansas a hoylake adviser said there have 
been no rulings in those cases which like the texas case were 
filed in late july 
