<TEXT>
turner broadcasting system inc announced friday a 
plan to refinance its 14 billion debt through sales of a variety 
of securities and from bank loans at lower interest rates 
tbs officials said in a statement that the company is filing 
registration statements with the securities and exchange commission 
to use proceeds from 900 million in securities sales to restructure 
the debt the rest would be borrowed from a group of banks 
tbs also will buy back all of its class a preferred stock in the 
cable news network subsidiary which is now worth 168 million 
the securities being registered with the sec include 300 million 
in tbs senior notes due in 1997 400 million in senior subordinated 
debentures due in 2001 and 200 million in liquid yield option notes 
due in 2004 
drexel burnham lambert inc will underwrite the senior notes and 
senior subordinated debentures while merrill lynch capital markets 
will underwrite the third offering 
tbs owns four cable networks cnn superstation tbs turner 
network television and headline news as well as an extensive film 
library the atlanta braves baseball team and controlling interest 
in the atlanta hawks basketball team 
